<br>
And, unfortunately, you seem to think that a government should be bound to act based upon the Gallup polls. We vote them into office to make decisions for the best interests of this country. <br>
<br>
We did not vote Bush into office to make coalitions that include countries that we KNOW are responsible for state-sponsored terrorist activities (see Syria, Saudi Arabia). The Bush administration is being too cautious with such countries. We have the moral authority right now to demand the results we require for success. Sorry, bombing Afganistan is not going to solve our problem. The reality is that there is a very serious threat to our way of life and those in power know how serious this is. Yet, we tippytoe around the subject of Iraq for example who most certainly is involved in these happenings. <br>
<br>
I think we are wimps for not immediately taking Iraq out. We have plenty of evidence of things they have done in the past. We have mounting evidence of the degree of their involvement with the Sept. 11 attacks.<br>
<br>
I think we are wimps because our media focuses more on the civilian loss of life in Afganistan than those who have perished in the conflict on our side (there have been military casualties). I am sure that there are horrible things that are happening to innocents in Afganistan. The problem is, in order to achive a military goal, it will happen. So, we have a choice, do not attack and allow the terrorists success and eventual victory, or take action and accept the civilian casualties as a very unfortunate, but necessary inevitability.<br>
<br>
I think we are wimps for pandering to some of these Arab countries (who were almost pleased at the results of the Sept. 11 attacks) because of MONEY and OIL.<br>
<br>
And I certainly suggest the government is more timid than the American people. Polls show overwhelming support for doing what is needed to end the threat, including inflicting (incidental) civilian casualties. Yet, I believe we are not doing what is needed. Only time will tell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/29/01 10:43:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Ending World War II</span><hr size=1> Funny thing about your post Wallace...<br>
